compileBlock()

Compiler.php : 1908

Recursively compiles a block.

protected compileBlock(Block $block) : void

A block is analogous to a CSS block in most cases. A single SCSS document is encapsulated in a block when parsed, but it does not have parent tags so all of its children appear on the root level when compiled.

Blocks are made up of selectors and children.

The children of a block are just all the blocks that are defined within.

Compiling the block involves pushing a fresh environment on the stack, and iterating through the props, compiling each one.

Parameters
$block : Block
Tags
see
Compiler::compileChild()

parseFunctionPrototype()

Compiler.php : 6472

Parses a function prototype to the internal representation of arguments.

private parseFunctionPrototype(array<string|int, string> $prototype) : array<string|int, mixed>

The input is an array of strings describing each argument, as supported in registerFunction. Argument names don't include the $. The output contains the list of positional argument, with their normalized name (underscores are replaced by dashes), their original name (to be used in case of error reporting) and their default value. The output also contains the normalized name of the rest argument, or null if the function prototype is not variadic.

Parameters
$prototype : array<string|int, string>
Tags
